                        <interp inst="t18441125-name-1089" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BRIDGLAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an omnibus conductor. On the 23rd of Oct., at ten minutes before one o'clock, I received information, and ran and caught the prisoner—he had this cotton—I saw him drop it—I said, "This don't belong to you"—he said, "No, I did not take it"—he was about 150 yards from Mr. Checker's—he ran part of the way, and then stood, and I came up to him.</p>
